ca.uqac.lif.cep.peg

Class ContextRef<Q,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uqac.lif.cep.Processor
      • ca.uqac.lif.cep.GroupProcessor
        • ca.uqac.lif.cep.peg.ContextRef<Q,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    Q - The type of the context value
    R - The type of the trend value
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ca.uqac.lif.cep.Contextualizable, ca.uqac.lif.cep.Duplicable, ca.uqac.lif.cep.DuplicableProcessor

    public class ContextRef<Q,R>
extends ca.uqac.lif.cep.GroupProcessor
    Group processor which generalizes the TrendDistance processor. Takes data in (a list for example) and extracts a context as well as a trend. The context will serve as a way for the processor to figure out which data to compare the trend to. The "figuring out" process will be done by the ChoiceFunction "func" which can be coded ad-hoc.

    A classic example is taking the value associated with the closest context in func's map. The trend and the value extracted from context can then be operated on with, for example, a subtraction and then compared like in the TrendDistance processor.

    Author:
    Alexandre Larouche
